column5: The day after being completely stranded by lighning and flash tornado like winds Cliff and I headed out to one of my good walleye lakes. We did try for some lakers but not five minutes after getting out on the lake the wind started to pick up and we had to find shelter....just so happens the shelter we found had some fish!      WINDY DAY WALLEYE  <iframe width="560" height="315" src="http://www.youtube.com/embed/ewy4HI8rRWo" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>       3 FOOT SWELLS EVEN OUT OF THE GALE FORCE WINDS                 BUT WE MANAGED A FEW FISH AND I HAD CLIFF EAGER TO TRY AGAIN WHEN CONDITIONS WERE MORE FISHING FRIENDLY                                            TIGHT LIBES ALL!
awesome walleyes, Simon. i went Saturday with my buddy, ifish4real on Rice and we managed a few walleyes too. Was a little challenging to find the weeds line but after that we had a great day.
awesome day simon nice eyes you had a little wind
